    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-02-06T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-02-06T19:00:00-05:00" n="238"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d238">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1–1246: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-06T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 6, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>232. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 53, Jan. 12.<note n="83"
                        xml:id="d238fn83">This telegram came from Tehran.</note> In view of
                    statements by Soviet Emb Tehran that calm prevails in Azerbaijan, please request
                    appropriate Soviet authorities to instruct Soviet military and diplomatic
                    representatives in Iran to issue passes for travel in northern Iran to Arthur
                        [<hi rend="italic">Joseph</hi>] Goodwin of <gloss target="#t_AP1">AP</gloss>
                        (<gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 132, Jan. 29<note n="83"
                        xml:id="d238fn85">This telegram came from Tehran.</note>) and such other
                    accredited <pb facs="0343" n="331" xml:id="pg_331"/> American correspondents who
                    may wish to visit Azerbaijan for purpose of reporting to newspapers in this
                        country.<note n="84" xml:id="d238fn84">According to Moscow’s telegram 442,
                        February 14, such a request was made in a letter to the Soviet Foreign
                        Office (811.91291/2–1446). In telegram 240, February 26, 1946, 10 a.m., from
                        Tehran, the Department was informed that the Soviet Consul had instructions
                        to issue no permits to foreign correspondents to visit northern Iran since
                        they would write “silly” stories on the situation there
                        (811.91291/2–2646).</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to Moscow, repeated to Tehran.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
